# Build-context root ignore for docker build (repo root is the context).
#
# Docker honours the .dockerignore at the BUILD CONTEXT root, NOT the one
# beside the Dockerfile (infra/vault-server/.dockerignore is only used if
# that dir is the context). Without this file, `docker build -f
# infra/vault-server/Dockerfile .` ships the ENTIRE monorepo — every
# workspace's node_modules, .next, .turbo — as context, which is gigabytes
# and makes the build crawl on "load build context".
#
# The vault-server Dockerfile runs its own `pnpm install` inside the build
# stage, so host node_modules are never needed in the image. Exclude them.

# Dependency + build output trees (large, regenerated in-container)
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.turbo
**/build
**/out
.pnpm-store

# VCS + local tooling
.git
.github
**/.vscode
**/.idea

# Tests + coverage (not needed at runtime)
**/coverage
**/*.test.ts
**/*.test.tsx
**/*.spec.ts

# Env + secrets (never bake into an image)
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example

# OS + editor noise
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log

# Docs + non-build assets that don't affect the vault-server image
docs
wireframes
apps/dashboard/.next
